comments.body:
@dukenv0307 Thanks for the proposal. Your RCA is correct. However the suggested solution will not prevent similar bugs from occurring but only reduce them.

> When we have a new action, if this action can have Reply in Thread option, no need to change anything. **If not we only need to add this to shouldReplyInThread**.

We could be adding a new action that should not have the reply in thread option without adding it to the `shouldReplyInThread` function since there is no enforcement.

@dukenv0307 This is not looking any different. 

> In the further when a new action is added, we only need to add this to NOT_ALLOWED_THREAD const if it doesn't has thread option

We can still add a new action and forget it to `NOT_ALLOWED_THREAD`
